cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.CE, cs.BIO

The paper discusses the implementation of maze solving in physical, chemical, and living systems, which involves the use of algorithms and control systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses the use of flow and chemical diffusion gradients, which are relevant to the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of substrates with maze-solving capabilities, which could fall under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper discusses experiments with slime mould, plant roots, and leeches, which are relevant to the category of cs.BIO (Bioinformatics).
